## Features

### Database (SQLite via SQLAlchemy)
- **Users table** — id, username, password_hash, full_name, role
- **Courses table** — id, name, teacher_id (FK), schedule, capacity
- **Enrollments table** — id, student_id (FK), course_id (FK), grade

### Student View
- See your enrolled courses (name, teacher, time, seats filled)
- Browse all offered courses with open/full badges
- Enroll in any course that hasn't hit capacity

### Teacher View
- See all courses you teach with enrollment counts
- Click into a course to see the full roster
- Edit individual student grades inline

### Admin View (`/admin`)
- Full CRUD on Users, Courses, and Enrollments via Flask-Admin
- Protected — only accessible when logged in as `admin`

---

## Project Structure

```
enrollment_app/
├── app.py              # Main app: models, routes, seed data
├── requirements.txt
├── templates/
│   ├── base.html       # Shared nav + layout
│   ├── login.html      # Login page
│   ├── student.html    # Student dashboard
│   ├── teacher.html    # Teacher dashboard
│   └── roster.html     # Course roster + grade editing
└── instance/
    └── enrollment.db   # Created automatically on first run
```
